    <!-- Consent dialog (first-run telemetry opt-in, DRAFT).
         NEEDS TRANSLATION: English placeholder copied in so DynamicResource
         lookups never resolve to blank text; swap for real translations. -->
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Title">Help improve ClickyKeys?</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Header">Help improve ClickyKeys?</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Body">We'd like to collect anonymous usage statistics to understand how ClickyKeys is used and prioritize what to build next. This is entirely optional and never affects how the app works.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_KeyloggerAssurance">ClickyKeys is not a keylogger. No matter which option you choose below — even Full — it never records what you type, your passwords, clipboard contents, or which specific keys you press or click. At most, it sends anonymous counts and settings; your actual input is never captured or transmitted. [NEEDS TRANSLATION]</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_FullTitle">Full — usage &amp; feature statistics</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_FullBody">Everything in Basic, plus how features are configured and used: panel layout and grid size, which display modes are on (transparent, rainbow background), whether colors/fonts/shortcuts were customized, gamepad settings, and aggregate key/mouse/uptime counts. Never your panel labels, exact colors, exact shortcut keys, or anything you typed.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_BasicTitle">Basic — anonymous identity only</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_BasicBody">A randomly generated ID (not tied to you or your PC), the app version, your OS version, and your interface language. Nothing about how you use the app.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_NoneTitle">None — don't collect anything</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_NoneBody">Nothing is sent to any server. You can turn statistics on later from Settings → Data Collection if you change your mind.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Footnote">You can change your choice at any time in Settings → Data Collection.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_PrivacyPolicyLink">Read the full privacy policy</sys:String>

